Linux Terminologly and Examples

Kernel: Glue between hardware and applications form example: Linux kernel
Distribution: Collection of software making up a Linux-based OS 
Boot loader(ön yükleyici): program thats boots the operating system. for example: GRUB and ISOLINUX
Service: program that runs as a baclground process.example httpd, ntpd, ftpd an named, 
Filesystem: method for storing and organizing files
X windows System: 
Desktop Environment
Command line
shell : command line interpreter that interprets the command line input and instructs the operating system to perform any necessary tasks and command
